===Etymology===
First attested in the mid 15th century. From {{inh|en|enm|accusative}}, borrowed from {{bor|en|xno|accusatif}} or {{bor|en|frm|acusatif}} or from {{der|en|la|accūsātīvus|t=of blaming}}, from {{m|la|accūsō|t=to blame}}. Akin to {{m|en|accuse}}. The Latin form is a mistranslation of the {{der|en|grc|-}} grammatical term {{m|grc|αἰτιᾱτική|t=expressing an effect}}. This term actually comes from {{affix|grc|αἰτιᾱτός|t1=caused|-ῐκός|pos2=adjective suffix|nocat=1}}, but was reanalyzed as coming from {{m|grc||αἰτιᾱ-}}, the stem of the verb {{m|grc|αἰτιάομαι|t=to blame}}, + {{m|grc|-τῐκός|pos=verbal adjective suffix}}.

